                  <floruit>He was the bishop of Constantinople and regarded as the greatest preacher of the Greek church. He lived a hermit live in the years <date> 371-377</date>. 
                     He was ordained  as a preist <date> 386</date> and then he preached in the church of Antioch for 12 years. Then , in  <date> 397</date> he became the patriarchate of Constantinople.
                     He was an extraordinary writer whose works were also translated into Gǝʿǝz . 
                    
                  </floruit>
                  <death>407</death>
